23/02/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader said Tuesday (22 February) that the government is collaborating with foreign intelligence agencies in an effort to locate fugitive General Ante Gotovina, one of the UN war crimes tribunal's most-wanted indictees.
Sanader reiterated that Zagreb would do everything possible to resolve the Gotovina case and prove its commitment to full co-operation with ICTY by 16 March, when the EU will decide whether to launch membership talks with Croatia.
In other news Tuesday, Sanader and a delegation visited the Vatican, where Pope John Paul II received them.
Sanader said the Vatican fully backs Croatia's EU entry.
(Vecernji list - 23/02/05;
HINA, HRT - 22/02/05)
